<P>A BRIEF HISTORY OF EPIDEMIC AND PESTILENTIAL DISEASES; WITH THE PRINCIPAL PHENOMENA OF THE PHYSICAL WORLD, WHICH PRECEDE AND AC|COMPANY THEM, AND OBSERVATIONS DEDUCED FROM THE FACTS STATED.</P>
<P>IN TWO VOLUMES.</P>
<P>BY NOAH WEBSTER, Author of Di&s;&s;ertations on the Engli&s;h Language and &s;everal other Works&mdash;Member of the Connecticut Academy of Arts and Sciences &mdash;of the Society for the Promotion of Agriculture, Arts and Man|ufactures, in the State of New-York&mdash;of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences, and corre&s;ponding Member of the Hi&s;tori|cal Society in Ma&s;&s;achu&s;etts.</P>
<P>VOL. I.</P>
<P>HARTFORD: PRINTED BY HUDSON &amp; GOODWIN. 1799.</P>
<P>[PUBLISHED ACCORDING TO ACT OF CONGRESS.]</P>
